Description: A circular jar-cover of pale grey marl pottery, with a conical top and central knob-handle. One side of the handle and one point on the edge of the rim are chipped.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 17
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 17 has been scratched into the object.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 64, 66 § 61,pl. xxxvi, 82)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.109-110, p.197, pl.39)
